etymologies: late Middle English: from late Latin qualitativus, from Latin qualitas (see quality)

definitions: relating to, measuring, or measured by the quality of something rather than its quantity

examples.text: a qualitative change in the undergraduate curriculum

shortDefinitions: relating to, measuring, or measured by quality of something rather than its quantity

definitions: (of an adjective) describing the quality of something in size, appearance, value, etc. Such adjectives can be submodified by words such as very and have comparative and superlative forms.
shortDefinitions: (of adjective) describing quality of something in size, appearance, value

examples.text: he offered free and qualitative education to the children
